{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 45954905, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2024-LOCAL-EYE", "title": "Organisation of two local European Youth Events (EYE) in 2024", "publicationDateLong": 1686700800000, "callIdentifier": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2024-LOCAL-EYE", "callTitle": "Organisation of two local European Youth Events (EYE) in 2024", "callccm2Id": 45955260, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43697167, "abbreviation": "EP", "description": "European Parliament"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43697187, "abbreviation": "EP-1-1", "description": "Grants in the Area of Communication"}], "topicMGAs": [], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43694065, "abbreviation": "EP-AG", "description": "EP Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "11 July 2023", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["05 September 2023"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3483014": [{"action": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2024-LOCAL-EYE - EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "11 July 2023", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["05 September 2023"], "budgetYearMap": {"2023": 220000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2023"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">ExpectedOutcome</SPAN>:<p>The expected outcomes of the action are to strengthen European citizenship among young people, make them aware about how the EU works and the democratic role of the European Parliament, and empower them to become active citizens.</p>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Objective</SPAN>:<p>The objective of the call is the organisation by two different organisers of local EYEs taking place over a weekend in two different EU Member States before the European elections in 2024.</p>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<p>The aim of a local EYE is to activate and inspire young people, and make them part of a conversation with European decision makers at the local level and pave the way for a long-lasting engagement. It should bring the EP closer to young people in peripheral regions of Europe, promote European democracy and create a two-way communication, raising awareness on what the EP does for them as young people and at the same time collecting ideas and expectations of young people from the local and national levels on the future of Europe.</p><p>A local EYE is organised under the EYE spirit and branding, and designed to be accessible (for young people who cannot afford travelling to Strasbourg to the central EYE) and inclusive (local EYE in national languages). A local EYE is a stand-alone event. It should not be organised as a sub-event of a bigger event (e.g. local EYE as part of a bigger festival and reduced to a tent of the latter). </p><p>A local EYE should also offer a diverse range of activities to attract as many young people as possible, and should not be limited to a single type of activity (e.g. a Parliament simulation) in order to allow a diverse audience to take part and reach out to young people who are less likely to already be involved in EU actions. Activities should not all be organised by the beneficiary, but co-created together with other youth and civil society organisations as well as public entities at European, national, regional and local level. Co-creation of activities with the European Parliament is also to be planned. These activities can be complemented by European Parliament\u2019s own initiatives. </p><p>A local EYE should, as much as possible, involve cross-border cooperation.</p>\n", "conditions": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-l